Heat oil over medium heat in a large skillet. Cook onion, bell pepper and garlic in hot oil for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in undrained canned diced tomatoes, canned corn, edamame and thyme. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until heated through. Season to taste with salt, black pepper and a few dashes bottled hot pepper sauce. Serve with additional bottled hot pepper sauce.